This notification should include ecotoxicity studies for fish and algae and full English translations of the ecotoxicity and biodegradation reports submitted in French.

Final Verified S64(1): Secondary notification under Section 64 of the Act will be required if the method of use changes in such a way as to greatly increase the environmental exposure of the notified chemical, or if additional information becomes available on adverse environmental effects of the chemical. This includes if the notifier wishes to import the notified dyestuff with an increased free copper concentration, eg FAT 40368/A with 4% free copper. In this case an algal toxicity test will be required. In addition, this notification is very site specific. Therefore, secondary notification may also be required if the notified dyestuff is used at another dyehouse with different waste water treatment procedures to those indicated in this notification.
